<br>
I have given long thought to Stampie and his admittance to our Elven Fellowship and Guild Hall.  In meeting Stampie and teaching him Elvish, I have been impressed by his heart and soul and his desire to live among the elves.  His renouncement to Rallos Zek and his warrior trainers has proven that he strongly desires our friendship and guidance.  I therefore passed on to him a token of membership within our guild.  I have spent long hours helping him to learn Elvish and teaching him more of Tunare, a difficult process considering our language differences.  To this end he has taught me Ogre, this may enable me to further Tunare's teachings among his people.<br>
<br>
I realize turning his back on Rallos Zek and accepting Tunare has alienated him from his homeland and his people.  He is no longer welcome to walk the streets of his hometown nor visit his family and friends.  We must strive to be kind to him, we must strive to become his new family.  A pleasent greeting in his native tongue may serve to meet his needs.<br>
<br>
In speaking of Eanin, I have sought the council of Mother Tunare and she has passed on to me that we must continue to help this wayward Paladin.  His imprisonment and escape, which he deems to be the work of Rallos Zek, may actually not be so.  We are to help him return to the enveloping embrace of Tunare.  Shunning him while in this state of turmoil would only send him further into the void he trys to fill by claiming allegience to Rallos Zek.<br>
<br>
Take Eanin in stride, be courteous and help him as much as you can.  In the end he will return to the embrace of our Goddess Tunare.<br>
<br>
Slaini, once again dons her helm and gloves.  Sealing the scroll with her personal seal she dispatches via the Antonican Bards for Kelethin and the young ranger.<br>
<br>
Take care and may Tunare watch over thee<br>
<br>
Slaini Litebringer<br>
Cleric of Tunare<br>
